Linley,<br><br>
Your words bring tears to my eyes.<br><br>
I will ask my daughter if she is interested in participating in this post, having had first hand experience with me, a Vietnam Veteran. If it were not for her support in my first steps toward acknowledgement and dealing with the internalized emotional pain, fear, and anger, I am not sure I would be where I am today.<br><br>
You present a very important and overlooked aspect of the Vietnam War, (&quot;the gift that keeps on giving&quot;), and that is the impact of the Vietnam Veteran's emotional state of mind upon his or her children. I am concerned about how much I have passed on to my children. Influence can be subtle and pervasive. What I have learned about myself is not very pretty. It is very immediate and real, and I know what I must do.<br><br>
Linley, you have a worthy cause and a real need. Please, persue this as far as you can.<br><br>

